                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City-policeman</hi>, 212). I was on duty in Smithfield on 13th March—the last witness pointed out the prisoner to me, she was running slowly—when she saw I was running-after her, she quickened her pace—I caught her, and the boy said she had robbed his sister—she said, "Pray do not lock me up"—I took her to the station.</p>
